@startuml entity_layer

package "Entity Layer (Domain Layer)" {

    ' ==========================================
    ' BASE ENTITY
    ' ==========================================
    abstract class Entity {
        # id : int
        # position : Vector2
        # velocity : Vector2
        # active : bool
        # layer : int
        + {abstract} update(dt: float): void
        + {abstract} render(): void
        + {abstract} getHitbox(): Rectangle
        + onCollide(other: Entity*, side: Side): void
        + isActive(): bool
        + setActive(active: bool): void
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' PLAYER
    ' ==========================================
    class Mario {
        + fsm : MarioFSM
        + lives : int
        + coins : int
        + score : int
        + isRunning : bool
        + facingRight : bool
        - coyoteTimer : float
        - jumpBufferTimer : float
        - jumpHoldTimer : float
        - isHoldingJump : bool
        - invulTimer : float
        - fireball1Active : bool
        - fireball2Active : bool
        + update(dt: float): void
        + render(): void
        + getHitbox(): Rectangle
        + onCollide(other: Entity*, side: Side): void
        - handleMovement(input: InputState, dt: float): void
        - handleJump(input: InputState, dt: float): void
        - applyPhysics(dt: float): void
        - shoot(): void
        - takeDamage(): void
        - die(): void
        - collect(item: Item*): void
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' ENEMIES
    ' ==========================================
    abstract class Enemy {
        # direction : int
        # moveSpeed : float
        # isDead : bool
        # deathTimer : float
        # scoreValue : int
        + update(dt: float): void
        + onCollide(other: Entity*, side: Side): void
        # {abstract} onUpdateAI(dt: float): void
        # onStomped(): void
        # onFireball(): void
        # onShell(): void
        # onStar(): void
    }

    class Goomba {
        # onUpdateAI(dt: float): void
        # onStomped(): void
    }

    class KoopaTroopa {
        + shellState : ShellState
        + reviveTimer : float
        # onUpdateAI(dt: float): void
        # onStomped(): void
        + kickShell(): void
    }

    class PiranhaPlant {
        + pipeCenter : Vector2
        + moveDir : int
        + moveTimer : float
        + waitTimer : float
        + hiddenIfClose : bool
        # onUpdateAI(dt: float): void
        # onStomped(): void
    }

    class Bowser {
        + fireTimer : float
        + hammerTimer : float
        + hp : int
        # onUpdateAI(dt: float): void
        # onFireball(): void
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' ITEMS
    ' ==========================================
    abstract class Item {
        + isMoving : bool
        + moveDir : int
        + update(dt: float): void
        + onCollide(other: Entity*, side: Side): void
        # {abstract} onPickup(mario: Mario&): void
    }

    class Mushroom {
        # onPickup(mario: Mario&): void
    }

    class FireFlower {
        # onPickup(mario: Mario&): void
    }

    class StarPower {
        + bounceVelocity : float
        # onPickup(mario: Mario&): void
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' PROJECTILES
    ' ==========================================
    abstract class Projectile {
        + damage : int
        + maxBounce : int
        + bounceCount : int
        # {abstract} onHitEnemy(enemy: Enemy*): void
        # {abstract} onHitTile(): void
    }

    class Fireball {
        # onHitEnemy(enemy: Enemy*): void
        # onHitTile(): void
    }

    class Hammer {
        # onHitEnemy(enemy: Enemy*): void
        # onHitTile(): void
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' PARTICLES (Visual Only)
    ' ==========================================
    class Particle <<Visual>> {
        + lifetime : float
        + velocity : Vector2
        + sprite : SpriteFrame
    }

    ' ==========================================
    ' INHERITANCE & RELATIONSHIPS
    ' ==========================================
    
    Entity <|-- Mario
    Entity <|-- Enemy
    Entity <|-- Item
    Entity <|-- Projectile

    Enemy <|-- Goomba
    Enemy <|-- KoopaTroopa
    Enemy <|-- PiranhaPlant
    Enemy <|-- Bowser

    Item <|-- Mushroom
    Item <|-- FireFlower
    Item <|-- StarPower

    Projectile <|-- Fireball
    Projectile <|-- Hammer

    ' Interaction relationships
    Mario ..> Item : <<collects>>
    Mario ..> Projectile : <<shoots/hit by>>
    Projectile ..> Enemy : <<damages>>
    Mario ..> Enemy : <<stomps/hit by>>
    
    note bottom of Particle
      Not a true Entity subclass. 
      Uses ObjectPool<Particle> and 
      has no physical collision.
    end note
}

@enduml

Key Enhancements Explained
Here is how the Entity layer classes break down based on your design document:

Entity (Abstract Base): The foundation for the entire Domain layer. 
Standardizes update(), render(), and polymorphic onCollide() logic. 
Tracks essential data like position, velocity, and rendering layer.

Mario: Contains the most complex localized state, managing precision platforming mechanics (coyoteTimer, jumpBufferTimer, jumpHoldTimer). 
It aggregates MarioFSM to manage form states (Small, Super, Fire, Invincible) cleanly without massive if/else blocks.

Enemy (Abstract Base & Subclasses): Employs the Template Method pattern. 
The base Enemy class handles standard physics and collision resolution in its update(), deferring specific movement logic to the pure virtual #onUpdateAI(dt) implemented by subclasses like Goomba or PiranhaPlant. 
Event hooks like #onStomped() or #onFireball() can be overridden (e.g., a Goomba dies to a fireball, but a BuzzyBeetle wouldn't).

Item (Abstract Base & Subclasses): Ensures items handle their 
own movement (like a Mushroom sliding or a StarPower bouncing) while 
defining the pure virtual #onPickup(mario&) to delegate the exact 
buff implementation to the specific item class.

Projectile: Abstracts behavior for bouncing items (like Mario's Fireball) 
and gravity-arc items (like the Hammer Bro's Hammer). 
Tracks bounceCount to enforce the 3-bounce lifespan rule described in the physics section.

Particle: Explicitly marked as visual-only to decouple it from 
the main CollisionSystem, reserving physics calculations solely for gameplay-relevant entities.